TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=557
TASK_TITLE=Add doey new command + smarter intent fallback for project creation
TASK_STATUS=in_progress
TASK_TYPE=feature
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W3
TASK_DESCRIPTION=CATEGORY: deep
MODEL: opus

TWO DELIVERABLES:

1. doey new <project-name> COMMAND
   - Creates project directory (~/projects/<name> or specified path)
   - Inits git repo
   - Creates minimal project structure (README, .gitignore)
   - Launches doey session in the new directory
   - Usage: doey new my-tui-app
   - Optional: doey new my-tui-app --path /custom/path
   - Should work from anywhere (no active session needed)

2. SMARTER INTENT FALLBACK
   - Current problem: user says 'doey we want to create a project about X' and fallback routes to 'doey masterplan' which requires an active session
   - Fix: teach shell/intent-fallback.sh and shell/doey-intent-dispatch.sh to detect 'new project' / 'create a project' / 'start a project' intent
   - When detected: route to 'doey new <extracted-name>' instead of masterplan
   - The Haiku model in intent-fallback.sh needs better prompt engineering to distinguish:
     a) 'create/start/new project' → doey new
     b) 'plan this feature' → doey masterplan (needs active session)
     c) 'do this task' → doey masterplan or instant-task (needs active session)
   - Should also handle: pass the project description/context to the Boss as the first message after session starts

BUG CONTEXT: User ran from home dir with no session. Fallback incorrectly mapped to masterplan which failed with 'Session doey-doey-2 not running'. The intent was clearly 'create a new project and start working on it'.

KEY FILES:
- shell/doey.sh — CLI entry, command routing
- shell/intent-fallback.sh — Haiku-powered intent classification
- shell/doey-intent-dispatch.sh — maps classified intent to commands
- docs/intent-fallback.md — intent fallback docs
